        "text": "FWIW I came to be interested in Datalog precisely  because it *didn't have* nested data structures. Nested data structures of arbitrary depth must be constructed and deconstructed using ordinary functional-style recursive algorithms, which goes against the whole philosophy of Datalog (in my opinion): performing _recursive_ relational queries (select, join, union, etc.) on flat datasets.",
